  <h2><b>HTML</b></h2>
  </div>
  
      <div class="concept-description">
 <p>HTML means Hypertext Markup language. HTML is made up of text content ("what you see"), mark up 
 ("what it looks like"), references to other  documents (such as images or videos),and links to other pages. <a href="https://www.udacity.com/course/viewer#!/c-ud721/l-3508959201/m-48724340">Click here</a> to see a reference 
   to HTML.
 </p>
 </div>
 </div>
 <div class="concept" id="lesson-1-3">
      <div class="concept-title">
      
  <H2><b>Tags and Elements </b></h2>
  </div>
     <div class="concept-description">
 <p>HTML markup is made up of tags. Tags are like keywords that tell a web page how to show content. HTML documents are made up of HTML <b>elements</b>. An element is everything from the opening tag to the closing tag.
 </p>
 </div>
 <div class="concept" id="lesson-1-4">
      <div class="concept-title">
 <h2><b>Inline and Block Elements</b></h2>
 </div>
 
  <div class="concept-description">
 
 <p>An <b>Inline</b> element is an element that takes up only the space needed. A <b>Block</b> element creates a sort of invisible box around the text that is being tagged. An example of a block element is the P tag, or paragraph tag, which creates a space before and after the text that is written.
 </p>
 </div>
 </div>
