     <h2>Avoiding Repetition</h2>
     </div>
        <div class="concept-description">
       <p>Avoiding repition is important in all aspects of programming. It is very important when writing CSS code because you don't want to have to copy and paste for every area of your web page to make the style look the same.</p>
       </div>
       </div>
        <div class="concept" id="lesson-3-2">
      <div class="concept-title">
     <h2>CSS and How it Works</h2>
     </div>
     
     <div class="concept-description">
     
       <p>CSS stands for <b>Cascading Style Sheets.</b> CSS is code written to control the "style of HTML.One of the key features in CSS is <b>inheritance</b>. Inheritance depends on the tree-like structure of HTML. Elements within HTML inherit text-like properties such as color, fomt, text-indent, letter spacing, etc. To make a font bold in CSS you select font-weight. Whatever style you put in CSS should reflect on your html document. A <b> selector</b> defines what a specific HTML tag will apply to. </p>
